  "title": "WSHO cum ECO",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<p>a) Report to the Project Manager. Responsible for the EHS systems and implementations.</p>\n<p>b) The detailed duties and responsibilities includes but not limited to the following:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee the project's EHS performance, administer and execute the organization’s WSH management system.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with all stakeholders, including EHS Manager on reporting of EHS matters, audits, programmes, initiatives etc.</li>\n  <li>Proactively demonstrate and promote EHS initiatives and culture throughout the organization.</li>\n  <li>Prepare &amp; execute monthly EHS Programmes.</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely submission of EHS reports and inspections.</li>\n  <li>Able to lead fellow EHS colleagues and work alongside project team to provide a safe working environment for everyone.</li>\n  <li>Support the company's system certification audits, internal/ external audits &amp; programmes and other relevant certifications as needed</li>\n  <li>To carry out daily inspections and recommending preventive measures to ensure compliance.</li>\n  <li>To lead and investigate all accident / incident, near misses and recommend preventive measures to prevent recurrence.</li>\n  <li>Establish emergency preparedness procedures and work with different agencies to participate in the project.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and review risk assessments, safe work procedures and all relevant EHS plans.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with government agencies, clients for all EHS related matters and reports.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper documentation of all EHS related documents, reports, training records etc.</li>\n  <li>Act as a secretary for the project’s EHS Committee.</li>\n  <li>To prepare and submit all relevant documents for all EHS related awards.</li>\n  <li>Develop &amp; implement environment &amp; health management plans.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and report on environmental &amp; health performances.</li>\n  <li>Manage all waste, pollution control and to conduct daily inspections to ensure compliance.</li>\n  <li>Ad-hoc matters as assigned by the PM which is necessary for the execution of the project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Registered WSHO certification from the MOM.</li>\n  <li>Registered ECO certification from NEA.</li>\n  <li>Registered ECMO certification from IES.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge in Environmental Impact Assessment &amp; EMMP (Added advantage)</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of post-registration experience in building construction. (HDB or public sector projects have added advantage)</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills and able to work with all levels of people.</li>\n  <li>Well versed in the WSH Act &amp; its subsidiary legislations.</li>\n  <li>Internal Auditor certification.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS office &amp; EHS related platforms.</li>\n  <li>Other WSH related certifications.</li>\n</ul>",
